HEADWORD: Pinguefaction
<hw>Pin`gue*fac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pinguefacere</ets>, <ets>pinguefactum</ets>, to fatten;
<ets>pinguis</ets> fat + <ets>facere</ets> to make.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A making of, or turning into, fat.</def>⟦br⟧
